5. According to description "If user input specified state variable value is equal to user input value and user input value is greater than zero and user input specified state variable value is greater than a specific date and address of user specified input value is equal to the address of the contract and user input value is equal to constant, the contract transfers user input value from user input address to the contract address. Then if user input value is equal to constant, the contract transfers input value from the contract address to user input address. If user input value is not equal to constant, the contract transfers calculated value depending on user input value to user input address.If not (user input specified state variable value is equal to user input value and user input value is greater than zero and user input specified state variable value is greater than a specific date and address of user specified input value is equal to the address of the contract and user input value is equal to constant), cancel the transaction."
